Module: PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 1: Create the Project Structure
Objective: Introduce packages, directory structure, and the SBT build system.
Concepts Covered:
    • Packaging
    • Folder structure (src/main/scala/...)
    • SBT basics
Task Description: Create the project folders exactly as shown and add an empty Main.scala.
com/
 company/
       etl/
            models/
            readers/
            writers/
            transformers/
            traits/
            utils/
            pipeline/

MODULE 2 — CASE CLASSES & DATA MODELING
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 2: Implement the Employee & EmployeeStats case classes
Objective: modeling real-world data using case classes.
Concepts Covered:
    • Case Class
    • Immutability
    • Typed fields
Task Description:
Create simple models inside models/Employee.scala.

MODULE 3 — TRAITS & ABSTRACTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objective: Introduce abstraction using traits.
Concepts Covered:
    • Traits
    • Interfaces
    • Generics
Task Description:
Implement three traits: DataReader, DataWriter, and DataTransformer.

MODULE 4 — FILE I/O, PARSING & VALIDATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 4: Implement CsvEmployeeReader
Objective: file handling and parsing.
Concepts Covered:
    • File I/O
    • Parsing CSV
    • Option for safe parsing
    • Validation rules
Task Description:
Read employee data from a CSV file and validate it.

MODULE 5 — COLLECTIONS & FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING TRANSFORMATIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 5: Implement EmployeeAnalyzer Transformer
Objective: Practice grouping, mapping, filtering, and functional programming.
Concepts Covered:
    • groupBy, map, filter, sortBy
    • Higher-order functions
    • Pure transformations
Task Description:
Compute statistics per department.

MODULE 6 — DATA OUTPUT & REPORT GENERATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 6: Implement ReportWriter
Objective: formatting output and writing files.
Concepts Covered:
    • Writing text files
    • String formatting
    • Encapsulation of output logic
Task Description:
Write department statistics to a .txt file.

MODULE 7 — ETL PIPELINE ORCHESTRATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 7: Build the Complete ETLPipeline
Objective: modular orchestration and combining components.
Concepts Covered:
    • Clean architecture
    • Pipeline execution flow
    • Dependency usage
Task Description:
Chain Extract → Validate → Transform → Load.

MODULE 8 — FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING EXTENSIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 8: Add Filtering Capabilities Using Higher-Order Functions
Objective: HOFs and function passing.
Concepts Covered:
    • Functions as parameters
    • foldLeft to chain filters
    • Functional purity
Task Description:
Enhance the pipeline with filter functions.

MODULE 9 — UTILITY MODULE & TEST DATA GENERATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 9: Implement DataGenerator Utility
Objective: random data generation and helper utilities.
Concepts Covered:
    • Random values
    • Utility objects
    • Writing CSV programmatically
Task Description:
Generate realistic employee data using Scala collections.

MODULE 10 — TESTING WITH SCALATEST
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 10: Write Unit Tests
Objective: basic testing methodology.
Concepts Covered:
    • ScalaTest
    • Assertions & matchers
    • Testing FP transformations
Task Description:
Write tests for:
    • EmployeeAnalyzer
    • CsvEmployeeReader

MODULE 11 — FINAL EXECUTION & DEMONSTRATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Task 11: Run Everything from Main.scala
Objective: how to integrate modules and run the ETL.
Concepts Covered:
    • Program entry point
    • Orchestrating entire app
Task Description:
Generate input → run pipeline → produce report.

